OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright start in places but
OL,6,Fsoon turning cloudier as rain spreads
OL,7,Feast in the morning. A drier afternoon
OL,8,Fbut with patchy rain in the west.
OL,9,FBright spells developing towards
OL,10,Feastern coasts where it will feel
OL,11,Fwarm. Breezy at times.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA largely dry evening with
OL,14,Flate bright or sunny spells in the
OL,15,Feast and winds falling light. Dry
OL,16,Fovernight with clear spells in the
OL,17,Feast but remaining cloudy in west.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
